result.execSummary:
The defendant Corey Matthew McCutcheon was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Corey Matthew McCutcheon is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Corey Matthew McCutcheon was found guilty of Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Penalties for Misdemeanors-Class "B"], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Apprs: CO: RMW for SRN, Rpr: Kasten, Clerk:Liddle.ADA:  Edward Minser   DF ATTY:  John M. O'Boyle   DF:  Corey Matthew McCutcheon appeared. Case called at 4:37 p.m. Atty O'Boyle recites agreement. Court reads charge and maximum penalty. DE pleads GUILTY to amended Ct 1 Disorderly Conduct without the enhancer  in 15CM348  . DE sworn. Crt reviews plea questionnaire and informs DE of rights. Crt finds DE freely, voluntarily and knowingly waives rights and makes plea. Attorney's stipulate to the facts. Crt accepts plea, finds factual basis and finds DE guilty of amended Ct 1 Disorderly Conduct without the enhancer in 15CM348. On motion of the State, Crt dismisses 15CM403. Sentencing arguments. Crt orders:

- S/W 1 year probation. Report to probation no later than noon on Monday, November 30, 2015. Bond will stay in place until reports to probation. 

-   Complete all other programming as deemed appropriate by the COMPAS assessment and the Department of Corrections

-   AODA and follow any recommended treatment.

-   Absolute sobriety:  Zero alcohol, zero controlled substances, zero prescribed medications (except as taken and prescribed for you by a physician) in your system, on your person, or in your possession at all times. This prohibition includes drug paraphernalia.

-   It is hereby ordered, as a condition of the defendant's bond/bail in the above-captioned case, that he/she have absolutely NO ABUSIVE CONTACT whatsoever with the complaining witness, or with any of the following named persons and/or locations, Ms. McCutcheon and The Wild Badger establishment in New Richmond.  The term "abusive contact" is hereby defined as a verbal assault or an intentional infliction of or threat to inflict physical pain, physical injury or illness, an impairment of physical condition, and /or sexual contact or sexual intercourse without consent.  

- DNA Sample, Surchage and Misd. Court Costs. To be paid over the course of probation.
